Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] networking: proxy Chrome Web Store requests via fennec-services

When the user installs an extension from the Chrome Web Store, the
request currently goes directly to chrome.google.com/webstore. This
allows Google to correlate extension installs with the user's IP address.

This patch routes Web Store extension requests through
https://ext-proxy.fennec.computer (a thin, open-source reverse proxy
in the fennec-services repo) when the user has enabled the proxy in
Settings → Services → "Route Web Store installs through Fennec proxy".

The proxy:
  - Is opt-in only (default: off)
  - Strips all identifying headers before forwarding to Google
  - Adds no logging of its own (verified in the fennec-services source)
  - Is self-hostable; users can point to their own proxy

TODO: Implement proxy integration. Stub for Phase 1.
      Full implementation tracked in: fennec-browser/fennec#42

PILLAR: Privacy / Transparency
JOURNAL: Proxied requests are logged as kFennecInternal in the Request
         Journal with note "Web Store proxy request".

---
